Description: Electric vehicle manufacturer of the Tango EV.
Full Description: Commuter Cars Corporation was founded to environmentally solve traffic congestion, for commuters, by commuters. Our signature vehicle, the Tango EV will be a major part of the $104 billion global smart commute market. With our over 2,000 wait-listed customers, we know the world is yearning for the Tango to be manufactured. The Tango solves the traffic congestion issue by being as wide as a standard motorcycle, while being fully electric at the same time. Measuring 39” wide, 8’6” long and 61” tall, the Tango can lane-split and park just about anywhere. Having the ability to go from 0 – 60 mph in 3.2 seconds, the Tango is one of the fastest vehicles on the market. One charge on the Tango currently lasts 100 – 120 miles with that expected to grow larger as we evolve. Coming in at roughly 3,300 pounds, 2,200 of those pounds come from under the floor, ensuring the Tango will not tip or flip over. The Tango secures its passengers via an FIA certified roll-cage, making it one of the safest vehicles on the market.  As the electric vehicle market continues to evolve and governments backing ESG/SDG, the Tango will become a viable commuting option across the world. With its unique design, amazing specs and being an environmental traffic congestion solution, the Tango is sure to grab the attention of any driver. Now is the time for the Tango to flourish, so join our team as we take over the global commute industry.

Description: Urban Farmer is a family of restaurants that all stem from the concept of a modern, yet inviting locally-sourced steakhouse.
Full Description: Urban Farmer is a family of restaurants — Portland, Cleveland, and Philadelphia — that all stem from the concept of a modern, yet inviting locally-sourced steakhouse. The Urban Farmer backdrop is warm and elegant, yet quaint and rustic visually telling the life-story of the hardworking, country farmer who marries the cosmopolitan art-collector. The result is a space that is at once a restored farmhouse combined with an eclectically sophisticated art gallery. Each location of Urban Farmer, though inspired by the same unexpected couple, each have their own twist that is uniquely original and authentic to the city it lives within. Urban Farmer’s menu continues the theme of juxtaposition as it appeals to every taste from simple to sophisticated. Their in-house butcher shop means that the whole animal is used in the most creative manner and with only the most meticulously selected heritage-bred beef, while Their sustainably-sourced poultry and seafood are equally well-chosen. Their steakhouse, however, is not solely focused on meat alone, offering an array of flavorful, comforting sides, soups and salads chef-inspired from the season’s abundance. Their beverage program also compliments Their food and concept taking its inspiration from early-American cocktail culture and proudly featuring local craft beers, a curated wine list and spirits with fresh ingredients to give them a creative twist.
